title: 'Stranger Things' star Millie Bobby Brown, 12, signs with IMG
text:
'Stranger Things' star Millie Bobby Brown, 12, signs with IMG Mary Ward twitter TWEET More 
Millie Bobby Brown has landed a contract at leading modelling agency IMG, at the tender age of 12. 
The Stranger Things actress, who was catapulted to international stardom when the show was released on Netflix last year, has signed with the top agency. The agency also has Gigi Hadid and Miranda Kerr on its books. The rise of Millie Bobby Brown The rise of Millie Bobby Brown

She is the breakout star of Netflix's Stranger Things but did you know that Millie Bobby Brown's first big break has an Aussie connection? 
It comes after Brown, who was raised in Bournemouth, England, featured in Calvin Klein's first campaign under the brand's new creative director, Raf Simons, unveiled last month. 
Brown was spotted in the front row at the Calvin Klein show at New York Fashion Week on February 10. Related Content 
Dressed in a black bomber jacket and ripped jeans, the tween was photographed hanging out with rapper A$AP Rocky. Other attendees included Karlie Kloss, Alexa Chung, Gwyneth Paltrow and Sarah Jessica Parker. A post shared by Calvin Klein (@calvinklein) on Jan 22, 2017 at 9:02am PST Advertisement 
The past 12 months have been huge for Millie Bobby Brown, the British schoolgirl whose family moved to Orlando, Florida when she was eight to set up a teeth-whitening business. 
After she was spotted by a talent agent at a showcase for her weekend drama school, the Brown family relocated to Los Angeles. But, after she failed to land any major roles, the family decided to go back to the UK. SHARE Pin to Pinterest Link Millie Bobby Brown attends the Calvin Klein Collection Front Row during New York Fashion Week on February 10, 2017 in New York City. Photo: Getty Images 
"It was tears, tears, tears," Brown told the Daily Mail last year. "We went through tough times." 
After she was passed over for Steven Spielberg's BFG , Brown's breakout came in 2016 when she was cast as Eleven in the Netflix series Stranger Things . 
From there, she became one of the biggest names of 2016, with talk show appearances, award nominations and a cool 2.7 million followers on Instagram. Deserved, given she posts content like this: A post shared by Millie Bobby Brown (@milliebobby_brown) on Jan 7, 2017 at 5:06pm PST Related Content
